<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/147: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-11T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 11,
                                        1927—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>87. Your 128, May 8, 4 p.m. The President approves President Diaz’s
                            request and Admiral Latimer will be instructed accordingly by the Navy
                                Department.<note n="43" xml:id="d451fn43">Col. Robert Rhea, on May
                                12, was appointed Chief of the Constabulary; and Col. Elias R.
                                Beadle, on August 20, was commissioned a general in command of the
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guardia Nacional de Nicaragua</hi> (file Nos.
                                817.00/4775 and 817.1051/164).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>